%3Cp%3EIn%20casual%20conversations%20with%20people%20in%20the%20alcohol%20industry%2C%20one%20thing%20I%20sometimes%20hear%20is%20that%20they%20don't%20necessarily%20buy%20into%20all%20the%20headlines%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-drinking-less-alcohol-bad-news-concert-venues-promoters-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Z%20isn't%20really%20drinking%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They're%20obviously%20self-interested%2C%20but%20they're%20not%20sure%20Gen%20Z%20is%20some%20special%20sober%20generation%20that%20will%20buck%20the%20trend%20of%20everyone%20who%20came%20before.%20Yes%2C%20Gen%20Z%20is%20drinking%20less%20right%20out%20of%20the%20gate%20than%20other%20generations%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgeneration-z-teens-what-theyre-all-about-2017-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunderage%20drinking%20rates%20have%20declined%20steadily%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20recent%20decades.%20When%20they%20do%20hit%20the%20kosher%20age%20threshold%2C%20young%20people%20aren't%20jumping%20in%20headfirst.%20But%20there%20are%20some%20signs%20that%20Gen%20Zers%20will%20eventually%20revert%20to%20the%20American%20norm%20as%20they%20develop%20a%20relationship%20with%20alcohol.%20Some%20older%20members%20of%20the%20generation%2C%20who%20are%20hitting%20their%20mid-20s%2C%20are%20starting%20to%20look%20pretty%20similar%20to%20millennials%20or%20Gen%20Xers%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20amount%20of%20booze%20they%20consume.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20are%20students%20that%20did%20not%20have%20a%20regular%20college%20experience%20because%20of%20COVID%2C%20and%20also%20social%20media%20is%20a%20bigger%20part%20of%20their%20lives%20so%20far%2C%26quot%3B%20Nadine%20Sarwat%2C%20an%20analyst%20who%20covers%20beverages%20and%20cannabis%20at%20Bernstein%2C%20told%20me%20in%20an%20interview%20earlier%20this%20year.%20%26quot%3BThe%20data%20indicates%20that%20once%20those%20people%20turn%2024%2C%2025%20and%20enter%20full%20working%20adulthood%2C%20they're%20sort%20of%20consuming%20like%20previous%20people%20would%20at%20that%20age.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrinking%20is%20a%20function%20of%20both%20economic%20and%20social%20forces%2C%20and%20Gen%20Z%20is%20playing%20catch-up%20on%20both%20fronts.%20Essentially%2C%2025%20is%20the%20new%2021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20cultural%20signifiers%20where%20Gen%20Z%20is%20behind%20the%20curve.%20An%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2023%2F05%2F23%2Fyoung-adults-in-the-u-s-are-reaching-key-life-milestones-later-than-in-the-past%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Pew%20Research%20Center%20found%20that%20in%202021%2C%2021-year-olds%20in%20the%20US%20also%20financially%20lagged%20far%20behind%20people%20of%20the%20same%20age%20in%201980.%20They're%20much%20less%20likely%20to%20have%20a%20full-time%20job%20or%20fully%20support%20themselves%20financially.%20But%20here%2C%20too%2C%20the%20younger%20generation%20is%20making%20up%20ground%3A%20By%20the%20time%20they're%2025%2C%20today's%20young%20people%20look%20similar%20to%2021-year-olds%20in%20the%201980s%20and%20are%20caught%20up%20with%2025-year-olds%20of%20that%20era.%20In%20the%20US%20Census%20Bureau's%202021%20American%20Community%20Survey%2C%20about%20two-thirds%20of%2025-year-olds%20said%20they%20had%20full-time%20work%2C%20like%2021-year-olds%20in%201980%20and%20only%20slightly%20behind%2025-year-olds%20at%20that%20time.%20Six%20in%2010%20said%20they%20were%20on%20their%20own%20financially%2C%20which%20is%20actually%20ahead%20of%2021-year-olds%20in%201980%20and%20in%20line%20with%2025-year-olds%20of%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20the%20economic%20milestones%2C%20you%20can%20sort%20of%20say%20that%2025%20is%20the%20new%2021%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Richard%20Fry%2C%20a%20senior%20researcher%20focusing%20on%20economics%20and%20education%20at%20Pew%20Research%20Center.%20%26quot%3BThey%20really%20do%20ramp%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFry%20said%20education%20may%20be%20partially%20responsible%20for%20this%20shift%20%E2%80%94%20people%20are%20waiting%20to%20get%20their%20first%20full-time%20gigs%20until%20they're%20finished%20with%20their%20education%2C%20and%20they're%20focusing%20on%20their%20studies%20instead%20of%20picking%20up%20part-time%20jobs%20along%20the%20way.%20Almost%20half%20of%2021-year-olds%20were%20enrolled%20in%20college%20as%20of%202021%2C%20Fry%20said%2C%20while%20back%20in%201980%2C%20it%20was%20only%20three%20in%2010.%20%26quot%3BClearly%2C%20schooling%20and%20college%20are%20a%20more%20important%20endeavor%20for%20young%20adults%20today%20than%20they%20were%2040%2C%2045%20years%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20Fry%20told%20me.%20There%20are%20some%20variations%20by%20gender%20%E2%80%94%20young%20women%20are%20caught%20up%20with%20their%201980s%20counterparts%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-men-work-less-financially-independent-salary-marriageability-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyoung%20men%2C%20particularly%20those%20without%20a%20college%20education%2C%20lag%20behind%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20either%20side%20of%20the%20college%20experience%2C%20Gen%20Zers%20are%20also%20hanging%20back%20from%20the%20workforce.%20On%20the%20younger%20end%2C%20teens%20aren't%20taking%20that%20first%20job%20that%20will%20propel%20them%20into%20adulthood.%20The%20proportion%20of%20teens%20working%20or%20looking%20for%20work%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FLNS11300012%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeen%20declining%20for%20decades%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%201980%2C%20about%2055%25%20of%20people%20ages%2016%20to%2019%20were%20participating%20in%20the%20labor%20force.%20Today%2C%20that%20number%20is%20closer%20to%2038%25.%20On%20the%20postgrad%20side%2C%20the%20share%20of%20people%20in%20their%20early%2020s%20in%20the%20workforce%20has%20declined%20over%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20Nicholas%20Tremper%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20Gusto%2C%20a%20human%20resources%20platform%2C%20said%20in%20an%20email.%20Because%20older%20workers%20are%20sticking%20around%2C%20they're%20becoming%20a%20bigger%20share%20of%20the%20workforce%20%E2%80%94%20and%20making%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-worried-unemployment-layoffs-recession-jobs-hiring-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eharder%20for%20younger%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20elbow%20their%20way%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20primary%20way%20workers%20advance%20in%20their%20careers%20is%20through%20job%20mobility%2C%20which%20opens%20up%20positions%20for%20others%20who%20are%20entering%20the%20workforce%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWithout%20open%20positions%2C%20Gen%20Z%20workers%20have%20not%20moved%20into%20the%20workforce.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20nonfinancial%2C%20more%20emotional%20adult%20milestones%2C%20such%20as%20getting%20married%20and%20having%20kids%2C%20Gen%20Z%20is%20following%20a%20long-term%20trend%20of%20people%20putting%20off%20such%20events%20until%20later%20in%20life.%20The%20number%20of%20people%20getting%20married%20and%20having%20kids%20by%2024%20has%20collapsed.%20The%20median%20age%20of%20a%20person's%20first%20marriage%20has%20gone%20from%2025%20and%2022%20for%20men%20and%20women%2C%20respectively%2C%20in%201980%20to%2027%20and%2025%20in%202000%20and%2030%20and%2029%20in%202024%2C%20the%20most%20recent%20year%20for%20which%20data%20is%20available%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Fdata%2Ftables%2Ftime-series%2Fdemo%2Ffamilies%2Fmarital.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20Census%20Bureau%3C%2Fa%3E.%20People%20are%20beginning%20to%20have%20children%20later%20in%20life%2C%20too%2C%20and%20even%20putting%20off%20the%20littler%20things%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-changing-american-car-culture-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esuch%20as%20driving%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FA4vFw%2F3%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22The%20number%20of%20Americans%20getting%20married%20by%20age%2024%20has%20dropped%20off%20of%20a%20cliff%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22446%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAveyshla%20Jimenez%2C%20a%2025-year-old%20publicist%20in%20Miami%2C%20told%20me%20she%20used%20to%20idealize%20what%20her%20current%20age%20would%20look%20like%20%E2%80%94%20a%20house%2C%20marriage.%20Instead%2C%20she's%20still%20getting%20settled%20in%20her%20career.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20necessarily%20that%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20traditional.%20It%20doesn't%20seem%20realistic%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20seems%20like%20I%20just%20entered%20the%20workforce.%26quot%3B%20She%20started%20working%20as%20a%20teenager%20and%20can't%20imagine%20what%20it%20feels%20like%20for%20others%20who%20are%20behind%20her%20in%20terms%20of%20job%20experience.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20expect%20everyone%20to%20have%20worked%20as%20a%20server%20until%206%20a.m.%2C%20so%20if%20I'm%20not%20where%20I%20want%20to%20be%2C%20I%20can't%20imagine%20other%20people%20my%20age%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20reasons%20that%20Gen%20Z%20feels%20less%20pressure%20to%20jump%20into%20these%20life%20experiences%20is%20fairly%20straightforward%2C%20said%20Jean%20Twenge%2C%20a%20psychologist%20and%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D095908a1241d3f10f1aad7a63c6f4c809cb97a516da7dcaf7a65359febd2bced%26postID%3D6802b64c18fa5330631e4f4a%26postSlug%3Dgen-z-delays-work-marriage-children-homebuying-delayed-development-2025-4%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FGenerations-Differences-Millennials-Silents_and-Americas%252Fdp%252F1982181613%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGenerations%3A%20The%20Real%20Differences%20Between%20Gen%20Z%2C%20Millennials%2C%20Gen%20X%2C%20Boomers%2C%20and%20Silents%20%E2%80%94%20and%20What%20They%20Mean%20for%20America's%20Future%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20Young%20people%20nowadays%20simply%20have%20more%20time%20to%20live%20than%20their%20predecessors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPsychologists%20call%20this%20a%20slow%20life%20strategy%2C%20and%20it%20happens%20when%20people%20live%20longer%2C%26quot%3B%20Twenge%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20life%20expectancies%20have%20crept%20higher%2C%20and%20people%20have%20started%20to%20get%20used%20to%20those%20longer%20lifespans%2C%20they%20are%20moving%20through%20life%20at%20a%20decelerated%20pace.%20Teens%20are%20putting%20off%20dating%20and%20driving%2C%20young%20adults%20are%20settling%20into%20families%20and%20careers%20later%2C%20and%20middle-aged%20people%20look%20and%20feel%20younger%20than%20their%20grandparents%20did%20at%20their%20age.%20%26quot%3BIt%20starts%20in%20the%20'90s%2C%20but%20it's%20kind%20of%20slow%2C%20and%20then%20it%20gets%20going%20through%20the%202000s%20and%20then%20really%20accelerates%20in%20the%202010s%20once%20you%20transition%20to%20Gen%20Z%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FFAoP3%2F3%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22The%20proportion%20of%2024-year-olds%20having%20at%20least%20one%20child%20has%20steadily%20decreased%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22446%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Z%20doesn't%20have%20these%20new%20attitudes%20only%20because%20they%20feel%20they%20have%20all%20the%20time%20in%20the%20world%20to%20grow%20up.%20They're%20also%20being%20raised%20differently%2C%20with%20more%20attention%20and%2C%20some%20would%20say%2C%20coddling.%20As%20parents%20have%20fewer%20children%20and%20later%20in%20life%2C%20they%20nurture%20them%20more%20carefully%2C%20which%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20delays%20independence.%20Gen%20Z%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fraising-kids-with-nineties-type-childhood-free-range-parenting-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunder%20more%20adult%20supervision%20than%20previous%20generations%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20their%20playdates%20were%20carefully%20watched%3B%20their%20parents%20have%20monitored%20their%20whereabouts%20on%20their%20phones%20%E2%80%94%20which%20may%20be%20safer%20but%20means%20they're%20not%20figuring%20things%20out%20on%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BParents%20are%20more%20hesitant.%20They%20are%20less%20comfortable%20allowing%20their%20children%20to%20be%20uncomfortable%2C%26quot%3B%20Haley%20Stephens%2C%20a%20pediatric%20psychologist%20at%20UVA%20Children's%20Hospital%2C%20said.%20Confidence%20and%20skills%20such%20as%20problem-solving%20and%20conflict%20resolution%20are%20born%20from%20discomfort%2C%20which%20parents%20and%20schools%20increasingly%20shield%20children%20and%20teens%20from.%20This%20has%20some%20good%20effects%20%E2%80%94%20young%20people%20are%20cultured%20and%20sensitive%20and%20aware%20of%20what's%20going%20on%20in%20the%20world.%20It's%20a%20positive%20that%20they're%20not%20drinking%20and%20are%20avoiding%20what%20are%20generally%20considered%20negative%20outcomes%2C%20such%20as%20teen%20pregnancy.%20But%20it%20also%20means%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Ftechnology%2Farchive%2F2024%2F03%2Fteen-childhood-smartphone-use-mental-health-effects%2F677722%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethey're%20having%20a%20hard%20time%20fully%20leaving%20the%20nest%20and%20are%20more%20anxious%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETechnology%2C%20of%20course%2C%20plays%20a%20role.%20Young%20people%20spending%20so%20much%20time%20on%20the%20phone%20makes%20face-to-face%20interaction%20rarer%2C%20meaning%20they're%20slower%20to%20develop%20that%20muscle.%20They%20avoid%20driving%20not%20just%20because%20it's%20scary%20but%20also%20because%20the%20party%20is%20on%20Snapchat%20or%20TikTok%20anyway.%20They're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-sick-leave-pto-mental-health-work-from-home-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egood%20at%20setting%20boundaries%20at%20work%20to%20protect%20their%20mental%20and%20physical%20health%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20they%20may%20boundary%20so%20hard%20that%20their%20boss%20starts%20to%20wonder%20whether%20they%20can%20handle%20the%20day-to-day%20of%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJessica%20Lautz%2C%20the%20deputy%20chief%20economist%20and%20vice%20president%20of%20research%20at%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Realtors%2C%20said%20this%20hesitancy%20to%20take%20the%20full%20leap%20is%20showing%20up%20in%20the%20housing%20market.%20While%20people%2018%20to%2025%20are%20just%20a%20small%20slice%20of%20homebuyers%2C%20when%20they%20do%20take%20the%20plunge%2C%20they%20do%20so%20closer%20to%20their%20families.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20looked%20at%20Gen%20Xers%2C%20we%20would%20see%20they%20do%20not%20want%20to%20be%20close%20to%20home%2C%20for%20instance%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20for%20young%20millennials%20and%20Gen%20Zers%2C%20this%20does%20seem%20to%20be%20much%20more%20important%20for%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELenny%20Zaleski%2C%20a%2022-year-old%20senior%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Dayton%2C%20plans%20to%20move%20back%20in%20with%20his%20family%20in%20Chicago%20after%20he%20graduates%20from%20college%20in%20the%20spring%20and%20starts%20his%20full-time%20job.%20It%20sounds%20%26quot%3Bcrazy%20to%20say%20out%20loud%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me%2C%20and%20isn't%20what%20he%20thought%20would%20happen%2C%20but%20it%20makes%20sense%2C%20given%20skyrocketing%20rents.%20%26quot%3BIf%20homes%20are%20out%20of%20the%20affordability%20range%20and%20a%20studio%20apartment%20in%20the%20city%20your%20job%20is%20in%20is%20%242%2C000%20a%20month%2C%20at%20a%20certain%20point%2C%20you%20can't%20just%20bootstrap%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20He%20acknowledged%20that%20living%20with%20his%20family%20is%20a%20pretty%20decent%20lifestyle.%20His%20grandparents%20are%20in%20the%20area%2C%20as%20is%20his%20dog%2C%20and%20it%20will%20let%20him%20save%20up%20for%20when%20he's%20ready%20to%20strike%20out%20on%20his%20own.%20And%20when%20he%20does%20buy%2C%20he%20plans%20to%20do%20so%20nearby.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWriting%20about%20young%20people%20always%20has%20a%20sort%20of%20old-man-yells-at-cloud%20bent%20to%20it.%20Every%20generation%20gets%20pinned%20with%20a%20stereotype%2C%20and%20everyone%20takes%20their%20turn%20at%20diagnosing%20the%20%26quot%3Bproblem%20with%20the%20kids%20these%20days.%26quot%3B%20I'm%20a%20millennial%2C%20and%20all%20we%20got%20to%20hear%20about%20is%20how%20our%20avocado%20toast%20habit%20locked%20us%20out%20of%20the%20housing%20market%20%E2%80%94%20not%2C%20you%20know%2C%20a%20global%20recession%20and%20a%20real%20estate%20meltdown.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-baby-boomers-wealth-income-home-buying-ownership-suburbs-kids-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBut%20just%20as%20millennials%20are%20somewhat%20begrudgingly%20aging%20into%20their%20parents%20and%20grandparents%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Gen%20Z%20is%20also%20coming%20around%20to%20the%20grown-up%20thing.%20It's%20just%20taking%20them%20a%20smidge%20longer%20to%20get%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20%26quot%3Bright%26quot%3B%20way%20to%20age%2C%20but%20much%20of%20America%20is%20stuck%20thinking%20that%20baby%20boomers%20should%20be%20the%20mold.%20As%20mentioned%2C%20younger%20people%20across%20generations%20are%20just%20moving%20through%20life%20a%20little%20more%20slowly.%20They're%20also%20aging%20into%20a%20very%20different%20world%20from%20that%20of%20someone%20in%2C%20say%2C%20the%20'80s.%20Technology%20is%20much%20more%20prevalent.%20The%20economy%20is%20more%20unequal.%20The%20world%20feels%20pretty%20unsteady.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20workplace.%20Managers%20and%20companies%20have%20launched%20all%20sorts%20of%20complaints%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-bad-office-etiquette-good-workplace-practices-succeed-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Z%20seems%3C%2Fa%3E%20ill-prepared%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-viral-corporate-work-job-satisfaction-survey-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimmature%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20their%20jobs.%20This%20may%20be%20true%20of%20many%20young%20workers%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20necessarily%20their%20fault.%20Many%20businesses%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-training-broken-gen-z-mentorship-companies-employees-managers-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edone%20away%20with%20robust%20on-the-job%20training%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20meaning%20entry-level%20workers%20are%20left%20to%20fend%20for%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20boomers%20entered%20the%20workplace%20with%20robust%20training%20and%20development%20programs%20and%20clear%20career%20ladders%2C%20things%20that%20organizations%20have%20dismantled%20over%20the%20years%20to%20save%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kenneth%20Matos%2C%20the%20director%20of%20market%20insights%20at%20HiBob%2C%20an%20HR-tech%20company.%20%26quot%3BIn%20such%20an%20environment%2C%20I%20would%20expect%20people%20to%20'grow%20up%20slower'%20because%20opportunities%20are%20fewer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrant%20Dutro%2C%20a%2022-year-old%20senior%20from%20Wheaton%20College%2C%20told%20me%20he%20thinks%20there's%20a%20level%20of%20%26quot%3Bsafetyism%26quot%3B%20in%20his%20generation.%20%26quot%3BTh