een%20a%20leader%20in%20scientific%20research%2C%20including%20a%20record%20over%20400%20Nobel%20prizes%2C%20much%20of%20it%20government-funded.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EResearchers%20said%20Trump's%20funding%20cuts%20might%20mean%20others%20in%20their%20fields%20will%20take%20their%20talents%20to%20other%20countries.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20also%20said%20aspects%20of%20research%20funding%20need%20overhauling%2C%20like%20transparency%20into%20spending%20taxpayer%20funds.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Peter%20Lurie%20first%20learned%20that%20President%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flist-of-universities-targeted-by-trump-administration-doge-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecut%20federal%20funding%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20his%20HIV%20research%2C%20he%20was%20shocked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20quickly%20realized%20why.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20see%20exactly%20how%20they%20identified%20the%20grant%20that%20I%20was%20on%20as%20a%20target%2C%26quot%3B%20Lurie%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20some%20mention%20of%20trans%20people%2C%20and%20that%20apparently%20is%20enough%20to%20kill%20off%20research.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELurie%20is%20in%20a%20group%20of%20researchers%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cspinet.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2025-04%2FAPHA%2520v.%2520NIH%252C%2520Final%2520Complaint_0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esued%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Trump%20administration%20for%20cutting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjay-bhattacharya-x-content-creator-national-institute-health-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Institute%20of%20Health%3C%2Fa%3E%20funding%20for%20a%20range%20of%20projects%2C%20including%20research%20on%20Alzheimer's%2C%20reproductive%20health%2C%20cancer%2C%20and%20diabetes.%20Lurie%20was%20on%20a%20two-year%20NIH%20grant%20of%20nearly%20%24300%2C000%20that%20Trump%20terminated%20on%20March%2021.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20%26quot%3Bcertain%20answers%20that%20might%20actually%20stem%20the%20HIV%20epidemic%2C%20for%20example%2C%20will%20not%20be%20found%2C%26quot%3B%20Lurie%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%2C%20scientists%2C%20and%20education%20policy%20experts%20told%20BI%20that%20Trump's%20abrupt%20freezing%20of%20billions%20of%20federal%20dollars%20might%20do%20more%20than%20block%20progress%20in%20scientific%20research.%20It%20could%20result%20in%20fewer%20Nobel%20prizes%2C%20more%20brain%20drain%2C%20and%20a%20handcuffing%20of%20AI%20innovation.%20They%20said%20the%20US%20could%20lose%20its%20edge%20as%20students%20and%20scientists%20take%20their%20talents%20to%20other%20places%2C%20like%20China%20and%20Europe%2C%20that%20would%20fund%20their%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20administration%20has%20said%20that%20universities%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-reshaping-americas-schools-investigations-funding-cuts-department-of-education-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edo%20not%20comply%20with%20its%20demands%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20axing%20DEI%20practices%2C%20are%20subject%20to%20funding%20cuts.%20The%20NIH%20also%20issued%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgrants.nih.gov%2Fgrants%2Fguide%2Fnotice-files%2FNOT-OD-25-090.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20April%2021%20stating%20that%20it%20would%20pull%20medical%20research%20funding%20from%20schools%20with%20DEI%20programs%20and%20those%20with%20boycotts%20of%20Israeli%20goods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20researchers%20also%20said%20there%20is%20room%20for%20improvement%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-school-choice-vouchers-education-policy-exeuctive-orders-anti-woke-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigher%20education%3C%2Fa%3E%20funding%20system%2C%20including%20a%20closer%20look%20at%20the%20burdensome%20process%20to%20receive%20funding%20and%20more%20transparency%20on%20where%20taxpayer%20dollars%20go.%20However%2C%20Lurie%20said%2C%20shutting%20off%20funding%20so%20abruptly%20will%20do%20more%20harm%20than%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20US%20and%20the%20NIH%20in%20particular%20have%20been%20the%20envy%20of%20the%20world%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20medical%20research.%20And%20what%20is%20already%20starting%20to%20happen%20is%20that%20the%20United%20States%20is%20starting%20to%20slip%2C%26quot%3B%20Lurie%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20means%20that%20there%20will%20be%20people%20who%20will%20go%20elsewhere%20for%20support.%20It%20means%20that%20there%20are%20people%20who%20will%20leave%20the%20country%20for%20lack%20of%20support.%20So%20I%20think%20that%20it%20absolutely%20endangers%20the%20United%20States'%20position%20as%20the%20global%20leader%20in%20medical%20research.%20And%20for%20that%2C%20we%20will%20pay.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%2C%20NIH%2C%20and%20the%20Department%20of%20Education%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227a334856-6837-474f-94d5-94832376fc55%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Once%20you%20lose%20your%20edge%20in%20this%20area%2C%20it's%20very%20difficult%20to%20come%20back'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20has%20won%20nearly%20400%20Nobel%20prizes%20in%20physics%2C%20chemistry%2C%20and%20medicine%2C%20the%20highest%20number%20in%20the%20world.%20Of%20those%20prizes%2C%20174%20scientists%20who%20worked%20on%20104%20of%20the%20prizes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nih.gov%2Fabout-nih%2Fwhat-we-do%2Fnih-almanac%2Fnobel-laureates%23%3A~%3Atext%3DYou%2520are%2520here%2CPh.D.%252C%2520U.S.A.)%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewere%20funded%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20NIH.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobert%20J.%20Lefkowitz%20contributed%20to%20that%20%E2%80%94%20he%20won%20a%20Nobel%20Prize%20in%20Chemistry%20in%202012%20for%20discovering%20a%20family%20of%20receptors%20used%20in%20about%20half%20of%20all%20medications%20today.%20He%20told%20BI%20that%20%26quot%3Ba%20good%20part%26quot%3B%20of%20his%20funding%20over%20his%20years%20of%20research%20came%20from%20the%20NIH.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20biomedical%20research%20enterprise%20in%20the%20United%20States%20is%20by%20far%20the%20leading%20one%20in%20the%20world%2C%20and%20the%20NIH%20is%20undoubtedly%20the%20biggest%20supporter%20of%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Lefkowitz%20said.%20And%20while%20the%20cuts%20themselves%20are%20a%20cause%20for%20concern%2C%20the%20uncertainty%20with%20the%20future%20of%20impacted%20programs%20is%20leaving%20universities%20scrambling%20to%20figure%20out%20their%20next%20steps%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20that%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20cuts%2C%20students%20and%20trainees%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20participate%20in%20ongoing%20research%2C%20which%20could%20lead%20them%20to%20seek%20employment%20elsewhere%20%E2%80%94%20including%20outside%20the%20US%20%E2%80%94%20to%20receive%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20bad%20situation%2C%20and%20I%20have%20the%20perspective%20of%20having%20been%20in%20the%20game%20for%20roughly%2060%20years%2C%20I've%20never%20seen%20anything%20to%20rival%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Lefkowitz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20Trump%20has%20proposed%20and%20enacted%20a%20range%20of%20policies%20that%20he%20said%20would%20put%20America%20at%20the%20top%2C%20summed%20up%20catchily%20with%20his%20campaign%20slogan%2C%20%26quot%3BMake%20America%20Great%20Again.%26quot%3B%20His%20administration%20has%20said%20that%20freezing%20funding%20at%20universities%20that%20do%20not%20comply%20with%20the%20administration's%20demands%20to%20limit%20campus%20activism%20and%20DEI%20practices%20reflects%20the%20administration's%20goals%20to%20put%20America%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20suggested%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftruthsocial.com%2F%40realDonaldTrump%2Fposts%2F114342374504628520%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Truth%20Social%20on%20April%2015%2C%20for%20example%2C%20that%20he%20would%20consider%20removing%20Harvard's%20tax-exempt%20status%20if%20it%20continues%20to%20fund%20what%20he%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bpolitical%2C%20ideological%2C%20and%20terrorist%20inspired%2Fsupporting%20'Sickness%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColumbia%20University%20agreed%20to%20Trump's%20demands%20to%20preserve%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-columbia-university-funding-cuts-protests-antisemitism-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24400%20million%20in%20federal%20funding%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20receives%2C%20but%20other%20universities%2C%20including%20Harvard%2C%20are%20holding%20the%20line.%20Glenn%20Altschuler%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20American%20studies%20at%20Cornell%20University%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20as%20Trump%20continues%20to%20escalate%20his%20funding%20threats%2C%20the%20US%20could%20lose%20critical%20talent%20that%20would've%20kept%20the%20country%20a%20leader%20in%20scientific%20innovation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltschuler%20said%20it's%20likely%20that%20other%20countries%2C%20like%20China%2C%20will%20soon%20start%20trying%20to%20attract%20American%20researchers%20by%20offering%20to%20pay%20for%20their%20labs%2C%20travel%2C%20and%20research.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20those%20scientists%2C%20at%20least%20some%20of%20them%2C%20depending%20on%20what%20their%20life%20circumstances%20are%2C%20may%20find%20that%20a%20very%20attractive%20option.%20So%20whereas%20for%20decades%20and%20decades%20and%20decades%2C%20the%20brain%20drain%20operated%20to%20the%20advantage%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20now%20the%20brain%20drain%20may%20operate%20to%20the%20detriment%20of%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20already%20starting%20to%20take%20shape%20%E2%80%94%20Emmanuel%20Macron%2C%20president%20of%20France%2C%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Ffeed%2Fupdate%2Furn%3Ali%3Aactivity%3A7319033056365793281%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epromoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20LinkedIn%20a%20project%20to%20attract%20international%20scientists%20to%20conduct%20their%20research%20in%20France.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHere%20in%20France%2C%20research%20is%20a%20priority%2C%20innovation%20is%20a%20culture%2C%20and%20science%20is%20a%20boundless%20horizon%2C%26quot%3B%20Macron%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltschuler%20said%20the%20US%20will%20probably%20not%20realize%20the%20impact%20of%20Trump's%20funding%20freezes%20for%20years%2C%20and%20at%20that%20point%2C%20it%20could%20be%20too%20late%20to%20repair%20the%20damage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20may%20lose%20a%20significant%20next%20generation%20of%20important%20researchers%20in%20medicine%20and%20in%20science.%20And%20what%20I%20would%20emphasize%20is%2C%20we'll%20never%20know%2C%20ever%2C%20what%20discoveries%20were%20not%20made%2C%26quot%3B%20Altschuler%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe'll%20never%20know%20what%20advances%20in%20technology%20were%20never%20made.%20And%20once%20you%20lose%20your%20edge%20in%20this%20area%2C%20it's%20very%20difficult%20to%20come%20back.%20It'll%20take%20a%20very%20long%20time%20to%20come%20back.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224945ef76-c03a-49d5-aa8f-671d2ee6ab19%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'It%20should%20concern%20everybody%20when%20those%20dollars%20are%20being%20cut'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChanging%20the%20way%20colleges%20receive%20federal%20funding%20isn't%20a%20bad%20idea%2C%20Beth%20Akers%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20conservative%20think-tank%20American%20Enterprise%20Institute%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20fair%20to%20ask%2C%20what%20is%20the%20appropriate%20amount%20of%20federal%20funding%3F%20And%20I%20think%20there%20is%20a%20sense%20that%20maybe%20the%20amount%20of%20funding%20for%20research%20that%20institutions%20have%20become%20accustomed%20to%20might%20be%20overly%20generous%2C%26quot%3B%20Akers%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20may%20be%20funding%20some%20things%20that%2C%20if%20taxpayers%20understood%20where%20their%20money%20was%20going%2C%20they%20might%20not%20be%20thrilled%20about.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Akers%20said%20the%20abruptness%20of%20university%20funding%20freezes%20has%20made%20them%20%26quot%3Bmore%20of%20a%20wasteful%20and%20destructive%20process%20than%20is%20really%20necessary.%26quot%3B%20She%20added%20that%2C%20had%20there%20been%20conversations%20over%20time%20with%20universities%20regarding%20funding%20cuts%2C%20researchers%20on%20ongoing%20projects%20would've%20had%20the%20opportunity%20to%20make%20plans%20to%20shut%20down%20or%20transfer%20their%20work%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20stuff%20that%20will%20have%20begun%20will%20have%20to%20be%20abandoned%2C%26quot%3B%20Akers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20it's%20not%20just%20science%20%E2%80%94%20technology%20is%20on%20the%20line%2C%20as%20well.%20Rebecca%20Willett%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20statistics%20and%20computer%20science%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Chicago%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20Trump's%20funding%20cuts%20are%20putting%20artificial%20intelligence%20innovation%20at%20risk.%20While%20federal%20spending%20on%20AI%20is%20fairly%20low%2C%20Willet%20said%2C%20the%20industry%20has%20already%20made%20a%20significant%20mark%20through%20projects%20like%20ChatGPT%20and%20using%20AI%20to%20advance%20biomedical%20research.%20Cutting%20more%20funding%20would%20stifle%20those%20advancements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20are%20investments%20in%20areas%20that%20are%20really%20going%20to%20help%20advance%20society%20and%20be%20of%20real%20value%20to%20the%20taxpayers%20who%20are%20supporting%20this%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20Willett%20said.%20Cuts%20to%20those%20programs%20will%20not%20only%20lead%20the%20US%20to%20%26quot%3Bmiss%20out%20on%20important%20discoveries%2C%26quot%3B%20Willet%20said%3B%20it'll%20also%20impact%20workforce%20development%2C%20as%20students%20will%20not%20have%20the%20resources%20to%20be%20properly%20trained%20to%20develop%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20technology%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20an%20administration%20that%20is%20so%20focused%20on%20keeping%20America%20at%20the%20top%2C%20it%20doesn't%20add%20up%2C%20Willet%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHaving%20taxpayer%20dollars%20help%20support%20and%20advance%20science%20is%20important%20for%20the%20long-term%20success%20and%20prosperity%20and%20security%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%26quot%3B%20Willett%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20that's%20the%20way%20we%20should%20look%20at%20federal%20research%20dollars%2C%20and%20it%20should%20concern%20everybody%20when%20those%20dollars%20are%20being%20cut.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aasheffey%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Easheffey%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%20at%20asheffey.97.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ehere's%20our%20guide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-research-funding-cuts-nobel-prizes-brain-drain-medicine-ai-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1745827561000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F680bef953fe8d392836425de%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-research-funding-cuts-nobel-prizes-brain-drain-medicine-ai-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Trump's%20funding%20cuts%20at%20universities%20are%20jeopardizing%20his%20%26quot%3BAmerica%20First%26quot%3B%20mission.%20The%20US%2C%20a%20leader%20in%20Nobel%20prizes%2C%20could%20start%20to%20slip.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A48%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-research-funding-cuts-nobel-prizes-brain-drain-medicine-ai-2025-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22America%20is%20dangerously%20close%20to%20the%20worst%20kind%20of%20recession%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Hot%20air%20balloon%20dragging%20an%20anchor%20over%20a%20downwards%20stock%20arrow%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F680bd8923fe8d39283642013%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20do%20not%20envy%20Federal%20Reserve%20Chairman%20Jerome%20Powell%20right%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2072-year-old%20former%20investment%20banker%20and%20longtime%20economic%20policymaker%20stands%20at%20a%20precarious%20crossroads.%20As%20the%20Fed%20chairman%2C%20his%20job%20is%20to%20achieve%20two%20goals%3A%20price%20stability%20and%20full%20employment.%20Usually%2C%20the%20trade-off%20between%20these%20two%20aims%20is%20clear%2C%20but%20these%20days%2C%20Powell%20has%20to%20perform%20a%20difficult%20balancing%20act.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20he%20needs%20to%20keep%20prices%20in%20check%20as%20the%20White%20House%20enacts%20dramatic%20tariffs%20on%20our%20biggest%20trading%20partners.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20he%20has%20to%20try%20to%20slow%20the%20uptick%20in%20the%20number%20of%20jobless%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20Powell%20addresses%20this%20conundrum%20will%20have%20massive%20effects%20on%20the%20American%20economy.%20Get%20it%20wrong%20and%20the%20US%20could%20get%20stuck%20in%20the%20dreaded%20%26quot%3Bstagflation%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20condition%20in%20which%20inflation%20is%20taking%20off%20at%20the%20same%20time%20the%20job%20market%20is%20getting%20weaker.%20It's%20nearly%20impossible%20to%20simultaneously%20address%20the%20%26quot%3Bstag%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20%26quot%3Bflation.%26quot%3B%20Policymakers%20obviously%20care%20about%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20dual%20mandate%2C%20but%20given%20the%20central%20bank's%20blunt%20tools%2C%20equal%20treatment%20by%20the%20Fed%20isn't%20really%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20leaves%20investors%20in%20a%20pickle.%20Over%20the%20past%20two%20decades%2C%20the%20stock%20market's%20playbook%20has%20been%20fairly%20obvious%3A%20Don't%20fight%20the%20Fed.%20As%20the%20Fed%20has%20become%20more%20willing%20to%20step%20in%20and%20backstop%20the%20economy%2C%20it's%20gained%20the%20power%20to%20stem%20even%20the%20harshest%20stock%20sell-offs.%20Its%20track%20record%20is%20impressive%2C%20too.%20Seven%20of%20the%20last%20eight%20bull%20markets%20%E2%80%94%20when%20major%20stock%20indexes%20rallied%20at%20least%2020%25%20%E2%80%94%20started%20when%20the%20Fed%20was%20cutting%20rates.%20Investors%20eventually%20picked%20up%20on%20this%2C%20snatching%20up%20stocks%20as%20soon%20as%20policymakers%20intervened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20do%20you%20do%20when%20even%20the%20Fed%20isn't%20sure%20what%20side%20it's%20on%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20Powell%20and%20his%20compatriots%20at%20the%20Fed%20have%20chosen%20to%20do%20nothing.%20They're%20taking%20the%20wait-and-see%20approach%2C%20hoping%20that%20clear%20trends%20%E2%80%94%20or%20a%20way%20out%20of%20tariff%20threats%20%E2%80%94%20will%20arise%20in%20the%20coming%20months.%20I%20have%20no%20answers%20for%20this%20predicament%2C%20and%20as%20I%20said%2C%20I%20certainly%20wouldn't%20want%20to%20be%20in%20the%20chairman's%20shoes%20right%20now.%20But%20I%20do%20think%20this%20moment%20requires%20us%20non-Fed%20members%20to%20think%20differently%20about%20our%20own%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EUnderstanding%20history%20is%20important%20when%20we're%20talking%20about%20the%20Fed's%20current%20rock-and-a-hard-place%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20decades%20after%20its%20creation%20in%201913%2C%20the%20Fed%20was%20the%20invisible%20hand%20on%20Wall%20Street%2C%20guiding%20interest%20rates%20through%20booms%20and%20busts%20without%20noise%20or%20fanfare.%20Central%20bankers%20were%20tasked%20with%20ensuring%20the%20stability%20of%20the%20banking%20system%2C%20with%20a%20few%20unofficial%20projects%20around%20keeping%20prices%20stable%20that%20were%20more%20extra%20credit%20than%20required%20homework.%20The%20Fed's%20job%20changed%20drastically%20in%20the%201970s%2C%20though.%20In%20an%20era%20of%20disco%20balls%20and%20poofy%20hair%2C%20the%20US%20economy%20battled%20one%20of%20its%20toughest%20tests%20to%20date%20%E2%80%94%20an%20inflationary%20shock%20from%20a%20surge%20in%20oil%20prices%2C%20and%20an%20unemployment%20rate%20as%20high%20as%209%25.%20This%20is%20the%20infamous%20stagflation%20crisis%2C%20and%20it%20was%20the%20height%20of%20economic%20misery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20basic%20problem%20with%20stagflation%20is%20that%20it's%20an%20incredibly%20difficult%20trap%20to%20climb%20out%20of.%20Corporate%20America%20is%20suffocated%20by%20higher%20costs%20and%20lower%20revenue.%20Businesses%20respond%20by%20cutting%20jobs%2C%20and%20as%20many%20Americans%20lose%20their%20primary%20source%20of%20income%2C%20they%20spend%20even%20less.%20Affordability%20suffers%20when%20things%20are%20getting%20more%20expensive%2C%20and%20as%20unemployment%20rises%2C%20people%20have%20less%20bargaining%20power%20to%20request%20raises%2C%20making%20inflation%20cut%20even%20deeper.%20It's%20a%20nasty%20cycle%20that%20feeds%20on%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20creates%20a%20rough%20situation%20for%20the%20Fed.%20The%20central%20bank%20can%20try%20to%20influence%20the%20economy%20in%20a%20few%20ways%2C%20but%20the%20most%20important%20is%20its%20power%20over%20interest%20rates%20%E2%80%94%20the%20cost%20for%20banks%2C%20businesses%2C%20and%20even%20average%20Americans%20to%20take%20out%20loans.%20Raising%20interest%20rates%20is%20supposed%20to%20address%20inflation%2C%20and%20in%20scenarios%20when%20inflation%20has%20been%20the%20clear%20issue%2C%20the%20Fed%20has%20usually%20responded%20that%20way.%20But%20with%20stagflation%2C%20rate%20hikes%20can%20crush%20businesses'%20profit%20margins%20and%20increase%20Americans'%20borrowing%20costs%20through%20higher%20mortgage%20and%20auto%20loan%20rates.%20Then%2C%20everyone%20spends%20less%20money%2C%20and%20the%20vicious%20cycle%20continues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22breakout-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FPzf3r%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22The%201970s%20were%20the%20height%20of%20economic%20misery%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22431%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Fed%20took%20several%20years%20to%20get%20the%201970s%20crisis%20under%20control%2C%20with%20Fed%20Chairman%20Paul%20Volcker%20ultimately%20delivering%20the%20decisive%20blow%20through%20a%20steep%20and%20painful%20period%20of%20interest-rate%20hikes.%20He%20figured%20that%20crushing%20the%20%26quot%3Bflation%26quot%3B%20would%20then%20give%20the%20Fed%20room%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20%26quot%3Bstag.%26quot%3B%20Though%20the%20Fed%20ultimately%20emerged%20stronger%2C%20with%20its%20dual%20mandate%20legally%20enshrined%2C%20the%20period%20also%20left%20deep%20scars%20on%20the%20psyches%20of%20central%20bankers%20and%20Wall%20Street%20economists%20alike%20%E2%80%94%20many%20of%20whom%20are%20still%20around%20today.%20So%20it's%20no%20surprise%20that%20the%20glaring%20similarities%20between%20our%20current%20environment%20and%20the%201970s%20period%20have%20caused%20quite%20a%20bit%20of%20consternation.%20This%20is%20especially%20troubling%20for%20Powell%2C%20who%20counts%20Volcker%2C%20the%20stagflation%20slayer%2C%20as%20his%20central%20banking%20hero.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilar%20to%2050%20years%20ago%2C%20an%20exogenous%20inflation%20shock%20is%20working%20its%20way%20to%20our%20wallets%2C%20this%20time%20through%20tariffs.%20Dramatic%20tariffs%20threaten%20to%20boost%20prices%20on%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20products%2C%20and%20like%20the%201970s%2C%20it's%20unclear%20how%20long%20these%20higher%20prices%20could%20stick.%20Yale's%20Budget%20Lab%20estimates%20this%20could%20cost%20households%20%243%2C800%20this%20year.%20The%20president%20is%20launching%20this%20trade%20war%20at%20a%20time%20when%20consumers%20are%20already%20in%20a%20weakening%20position%3A%20Economic%20growth%20projections%20from%20the%20Atlanta%20Fed's%20GDPNow%20estimate%20that%20first-quarter%20consumer%20spending%20stagnated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20concerns%20about%20stagflation%20are%20also%20acute%20because%20the%20inflation%20crisis%20of%202022%20looms%20large%20in%20the%20Fed's%20mind.%20One-third%20of%20the%20Fed's%20current%20voting%20members%20were%20behind%20the%20decision%20to%20keep%20interest%20rates%20low%20through%202021%20as%20bond%20markets%20sounded%20the%20alarm%20over%20inflation.%20While%20Powell%20and%20company%20are%20determined%20to%20get%20it%20right%20this%20time%2C%20they%20are%20also%20aware%20of%20the%20pickle%3A%20Ninety-eight%20percent%20of%20Fed%20members%20said%20in%20March%20that%20higher%20inflation%20is%20a%20bigger%20risk%20going%20forward%20than%20deflation%2C%20while%2095%25%20cited%20higher%20unemployment%20as%20the%20prevailing%20risk%20in%20the%20job%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22breakout-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F3y2sO%2F2%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Stagflation%20risks%20rise%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22507%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20investors%2C%20stagflation%20also%20presents%20some%20nasty%20possibilities.%20Prices%20rise%20and%20revenue%20slows.%20People%20flee%20the%20stock%20market%20because%20companies%20can't%20maintain%20profit%20margins.%20They%20also%20shun%20bonds%20because%20fixed%20income%20often%20can't%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20pace%20of%20price%20increases.%20Tangible%20assets%20like%20gold%20and%20oil%20turn%20into%20safe%20havens%2C%20but%20even%20their%20values%20are%20roiled%20by%20violent%20changes%20in%20supply%20and%20demand.%20You%20can't%20find%20anywhere%20to%20hide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20live%20in%20stressful%20times%2C%20so%20let%20me%20offer%20you%20some%20comforting%20words.%20Reciprocal%20tariffs%20have%20effectively%20frozen%20consumers%20and%20businesses%20alike.%20It's%20possible%20we're%20in%20a%20recession%20right%20now.%20But%20a%20sudden%20shock%20could%20mean%20some%20important%20counterbalances%20are%20at%20play.%20There's%20a%20chance%20that%20retailers%20and%20factories%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20pass%20along%20these%20costs%20to%20consumers%20because%20demand%20is%20already%20sliding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20prices%20can't%20go%20up%2C%20that%20could%20head%20off%20any%20increase%20in%20the%20rate%20of%20inflation.%20That%20dynamic%20is%20why%20actual%20stagflation%20is%20rare%20%E2%80%94%20as%20in%20four%20quarters%20in%20the%20last%2055%20years%20rare.%20The%20%26quot%3Bstag%26quot%3B%20often%20takes%20care%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bflation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20I%20do%20worry%20about%2C%20though%2C%20is%20the%20Fed's%20inability%20to%20react%20to%20economic%20weakness%20or%20surging%20inflation.%20In%20an%20ideal%20world%2C%20the%20Fed%20should%20be%20able%20to%20proactively%20balance%20the%20economy%20and%20protect%20against%20future%20risks.%20A%20year%20ago%2C%20this%20ideal%20world%20was%20within%20reach.%20The%20Fed%20started%20lowering%20interest%20rates%20in%20September%2C%20even%20though%20unemployment%20was%20historically%20low%20%E2%80%94%20a%20nod%20to%20a%20victory%20over%20COVID-era%20inflation.%20The%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20jumped%2020%25%20for%20two%20consecutive%20years%2C%20in%20part%20because%20policymakers%20were%20able%20to%20effectively%20steer%20through%20the%20rough%20waters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20the%20case%20anymore.%20The%20Fed%20is%20in%20a%20reactive%20position.%20It%20can't%20risk%20taking%20action%20to%20get%20ahead%20of%20potential%20tariff%20inflation%20for%20fear%20of%20hurting%20the%20labor%20market%2C%20and%20it%20can't%20provide%20confidence-boosting%20interest-rate%20cuts%20for%20fear%20of%20reignited%20price%20hikes.%20Powell's%20hands%20are%20tied.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20central%20bank%20response%2C%20Americans%20could%20look%20to%20the%20federal%20government%20to%20try%20to%20ease%20some%20of%20the%20job%20market%20concerns.%20But%20given%20that%20the%20Trump%20administration%20is%20hell-bent%20on%20cutting%20costs%20and%20government%20headcounts%2C%20it's%20unlikely%20that%20avenue%20of%20relief%20is%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20a%20stretch%20to%20think%20that%20markets%20may%20be%20on%20their%20own%20to%20absorb%20any%20extreme%20changes%20in%20economic%20conditions.%20For%20you%2C%20that%20means%20potentially%20steeper%20ups%20and%20downs%20in%20the%20stock%20and%20bond%20markets.%20We've%20already%20gotten%20a%20taste%20of%20that%20recent%2C%20as%20investors%20were%20forced%20to%20deal%20with%20some%20of%20the%20most%20volatile%20weeks%20in%20history%20for%20stocks%20and%20yields.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20investors%2C%20our%20job%20is%20to%20take%20measured%20risks%20with%20our%20money%20to%20build%20wealth%20over%20time.%20Many%20people%20do%20this%20best%20by%20taking%20a%20largely%20passive%20approach%3A%20tossing%20a%20set%20amount%20of%20money%20into%20the%20stock%20market%20on%20a%20set%20schedule%2C%20not%20buying%20or%20selling%20on%20every%20Fed%20headline%20or%20speaker%20comment.%20However%2C%20we%20are%20humans%2C%20not%20AI-powered%20robots.%20We%20can't%20always%20keep%20our%20emotions%20in%20check%20when%20markets%20are%20swinging.%20If%20the%20Fed%20is%20frozen%2C%20we%20have%20to%20take%20it%20upon%20ourselves%20to%20set%20an%20investing%20plan%20and%20do%20everything%20we%20can%20to%20stick%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22breakout-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fh3XRI%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Buying%20low%2C%20selling%20high%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22354%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EFed%20policy%20also%20has%20a%20big%20influence%20on%20how%20we%20experience%20our%20lives%2C%20even%20if%20we're%20just%20casual%20observers%20of%20market%20headlines%20or%20occasional%20index%20fund%20dabblers.%20The%20Fed%20controls%20affordability%20%E2%80%94%20do%20you%20have%20cash%20in%20a%20savings%20account%3F%20The%20Fed's%20decisions%20could%20impact%20the%20rate%20you%20make%20relative%20to%20inflation.%20Are%20you%20in%20the%20market%20for%20a%20new%20house%3F%20The%20Fed's%20policy%20could%20indirectly%20impact%20long-term%20interest%20rates%2C%20which%20feed%20into%20those%20sky-high%20mortgage%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20are%20not%20powerless%20in%20this%20situation.%20Stocks%20are%20your%20best%20tool%20for%20fighting%20inflation%20over%20time%20%E2%80%94%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20has%20beaten%20inflation%20in%20five%20out%20of%20the%20last%20seven%20decades.%20Many%20of%20us%20can%20afford%20to%20take