0between%20April%2022%20and%20June%206.%20Here%20is%20a%20detailed%20guide%20on%20how%20to%20redeem%20codes%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ftechnology%2Ftech-news%2Fbgmi-official-redeem-codes-new-set-of-codes-to-get-weapon-upgrades-skins-125042800180_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22NATO%20can't%20ignore%20the%20Russian%20military's%20faster%2C%20more%20dangerous%20kill%20chain%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224217%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Russian%20rocket%20launcher%20is%20seen%20firing%20at%20a%20Belarusian%20military%20training%20range%20in%202022.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F680b2e0a3fe8d39283640a95%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222281%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Russian%20rocket%20launcher%20is%20seen%20firing%20at%20a%20Belarusian%20military%20range%20in%202022.%20Russia%20has%20vastly%20improved%20its%20artillery%20kill%20chain%20since%20its%20early%20failures%20of%20the%20war.%3Cp%3ERussian%20Defense%20Ministry%20Press%20Service%20via%20AP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERussia's%20artillery%20strikes%20were%20bizarrely%20ineffective%20in%20the%20early%20stages%20of%20the%20war%2C%20but%20that's%20changed.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAnalysts%20say%20several%20major%20overhauls%20have%20helped%20Russia%20make%20its%20kill%20chain%20faster%20and%20more%20precise.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENATO%20would%20have%20to%20learn%20quickly%20to%20prepare%20for%20a%20more%20experienced%20and%20refined%20Russian%20artillery%20complex.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20kill%20chain%2C%20or%20how%20quickly%20the%20army%20moves%20from%20finding%20a%20target%20to%20firing%20on%20it%2C%20is%20now%20far%20more%20responsive%20and%20precise%20than%20it%20was%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFederico%20Borsari%2C%20a%20resident%20fellow%20researching%20war%20technology%20and%20innovation%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20European%20Policy%20Analysis%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Russians%20are%20adapting%2C%20and%20this%20is%20definitely%20something%20that%20NATO%20is%20noticing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20is%20outpacing%20the%20West%20in%20artillery%20production%2C%20raising%20the%20prospect%20that%20NATO%20must%20deter%20an%20adversary%20with%20more%20battlefield%20firepower%20and%20the%20fleets%20of%20reconnaissance%20drones%20that%20guide%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2268de8a10-1d90-4972-892c-3a39160066cc%5C%22%3ERussia's%20rough%20start%20to%20the%20war%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225103%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Russian%20soldier%20looks%20into%20a%20targeting%20apparatus%20for%20a%20heavy%20gun.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F680b2fb4a466d2b74ab42270%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222845%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussian%20troops%20attend%20artillery%20and%20combat%20training%20at%20a%20Belarusian%20military%20firing%20range.%3Cp%3ERussian%20Defense%20Ministry%20Press%20Service%20via%20AP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20more%20serious%20problems%20for%20Russia%20early%20in%20the%20conflict%20was%20that%20the%20time%20between%20finding%20a%20target%20and%20firing%20on%20it%20was%20far%20too%20slow.%20It%20took%20hours%20for%20indirect%20fires%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-is-now-relying-heavy-artillery-to-batter-ukraine-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eartillery%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20mortars%2C%20and%20even%20longer%20for%20cruise%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBorsari%20wrote%20in%20a%20report%20published%20in%20early%20April%20that%20Russian%20strikes%20were%20sometimes%20delayed%20by%20up%20to%20four%20hours%2C%20making%20them%20ineffective%20against%20Ukrainian%20units%20that%20had%20long%20since%20moved%20on%20to%20a%20new%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20case%20of%20the%20tactical%20ballistic%20missile%2C%20this%20was%20very%20much%20the%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BSometimes%2C%20it%20took%20even%20longer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20at%20the%20London-based%20Royal%20United%20Services%20Institute%20think%20tank%20wrote%20in%20November%202022%20that%20Russian%20forces%20%26quot%3Bhave%20missed%20targets%20because%20of%20self-imposed%20frictions%20in%20their%20kill%20chains%2C%20usually%20striking%20too%20late%20rather%20than%20not%20at%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20challenge%20is%20that%20Russia's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-is-getting-better-at-rapidly-destroying-enemy-artillery-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereconnaissance%20strike%20complex%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20ineffective%2C%20dependent%20on%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eaging%20satellites%20and%20a%20smattering%20of%20drones%20that%20couldn't%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20pace%20of%20the%20fighting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20used%20surveillance%20drones%20like%20the%20Orlan-10%20and%20Forpost%20early%20in%20its%20invasion%2C%20as%20evidenced%20by%20Oryx's%20open-source%20records%20showing%20several%20were%20destroyed%20in%20the%20spring%20of%202022.%20But%20there%20were%20too%20few%20of%20these%20intelligence%2C%20surveillance%2C%20and%20reconnaissance%20(ISR)%20assets%20to%20be%20effective.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETarget%20selection%20suffered.%20Sometimes%2C%20the%20invading%20Russians%20would%20waste%20tactical%20missiles%20on%20small%20groups%20of%20Ukrainian%20infantry%20while%20peppering%20vast%20airfields%20with%20a%20handful%20of%20cruise%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20issue%20was%20that%20Russia's%20early%20command%20and%20control%20systems%20were%20too%20rigid%2C%20outdated%2C%20and%20confused%2C%20carrying%20the%20top-down%20hallmarks%20of%20the%20Soviet%20command%20structure.%20After%20collecting%20timely%20intelligence%2C%20troops%20on%20the%20ground%20had%20to%20wait%20for%20strikes%20to%20get%20approved%20through%20different%20rungs%20of%20command.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20confusion%20only%20slowed%20that%20down.%20Many%20Russian%20soldiers%20and%20officers%20were%20also%20often%20unclear%20on%20their%20responsibility%20areas%2C%20problems%20that%20were%20exacerbated%20by%20communication%20and%20tech%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22550%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20soldier%20is%20seen%20using%20a%20Strelets%20laptop%20that%20helps%20with%20targeting%20for%20artillery%20fire.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F680b2ee53fe8d39283640a96%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22390%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDuring%20the%20early%20full-scale%20invasion%2C%20Russian%20units%20didn't%20have%20the%20Strelets%20in%20many%20cases.%3Cp%3ERussian%20Defense%20Ministry%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20in%20the%20early%20war%2C%20many%20Russian%20units%20didn't%20have%20the%20Strelets%20laptops%20that%20allowed%20them%20to%20target%20Ukrainian%20forces%20effectively%2C%20RUSI%20researchers%20wrote%20in%20May%202023.%20The%20software%20consolidates%20intelligence%20data%20from%20drones%20and%20recon%20units%2C%20displaying%20it%20on%20a%20live%20map%20for%20commanders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20Russian%20units%20that%20did%20have%20the%20computers%2C%20the%20researchers%20wrote%2C%20often%20left%20them%20sitting%20in%20baggage%20or%20didn't%20know%20how%20to%20set%20them%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fd5ab0f5-a28d-4a81-9f34-a52891f16c9a%5C%22%3EHow%20Russia%20fixed%20its%20kill%20chain%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Russia%20uses%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20tactical%20drones%20to%20acquire%20targets%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20flooding%20the%20airspace%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-keeps-orlan10-drone-flying-over-ukraine-with-w