't%20think%20scaling%20AI%20is%20enough%20to%20make%20it%20smarter.%3Cp%3EMeta%20Platforms%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EYann%20LeCun%2C%20chief%20AI%20scientist%20at%20Meta%2C%20pushed%20back%20against%20%26quot%3Bscaling%20laws.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThese%20laws%20say%20that%20the%20bigger%20AI%20models%20are%2C%20the%20more%20high-performing%20and%20smarter%20they%20will%20be.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20just%20about%20scaling%20anymore%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20at%20a%20talk%20in%20Singapore.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%20the%20AI%20industry%20has%20abided%20by%20a%20set%20of%20principles%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bscaling%20laws.%26quot%3B%20OpenAI%20researchers%20outlined%20them%20in%20the%20seminal%202020%20paper%2C%20%26quot%3BScaling%20Laws%20for%20Neural%20Language%20Models.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BModel%20performance%20depends%20most%20strongly%20on%20scale%2C%20which%20consists%20of%20three%20factors%3A%20the%20number%20of%20model%20parameters%20N%20(excluding%20embeddings)%2C%20the%20size%20of%20the%20dataset%20D%2C%20and%20the%20amount%20of%20compute%20C%20used%20for%20training%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20essence%2C%20more%20is%20more%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20building%20highly%20intelligent%20AI.%20This%20idea%20has%20fueled%20huge%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-invest-billions-into-japan-ai-data-centers-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvestments%20in%20data%20centers%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20allow%20AI%20models%20to%20process%20and%20learn%20from%20huge%20amounts%20of%20existing%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20recently%2C%20AI%20experts%20across%20Silicon%20Valley%20have%20started%20to%20challenge%20that%20doctrine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20interesting%20problems%20scale%20extremely%20badly%2C%26quot%3B%20Meta's%20chief%20AI%20scientist%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-yann-lecun-france-attract-scientists-us-trump-funding-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYann%20LeCun%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20at%20the%20National%20University%20of%20Singapore%20on%20Sunday.%20%26quot%3BYou%20cannot%20just%20assume%20that%20more%20data%20and%20more%20compute%20means%20smarter%20AI.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeCun's%20point%20hinges%20on%20the%20idea%20that%20training%20AI%20on%20vast%20amounts%20of%20basic%20subject%20matter%2C%20like%20internet%20data%2C%20won't%20lead%20to%20some%20sort%20of%20superintelligence.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESmart%20AI%20is%20a%20different%20breed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20mistake%20is%20that%20very%20simple%20systems%2C%20when%20they%20work%20for%20simple%20problems%2C%20people%20extrapolate%20them%20to%20think%20that%20they'll%20work%20for%20complex%20problems%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20do%20some%20amazing%20things%2C%20but%20that%20creates%20a%20religion%20of%20scaling%20that%20you%20just%20need%20to%20scale%20systems%20more%20and%20they're%20going%20to%20naturally%20become%20more%20intelligent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20the%20impact%20of%20scaling%20is%20magnified%20because%20many%20of%20the%20latest%20breakthroughs%20in%20AI%20are%20actually%20%26quot%3Breally%20easy%2C%26quot%3B%20LeCun%20said.%20The%20biggest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-openai-ai-dictionary-help-understand-nvidia-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elarge%20language%20models%3C%2Fa%3E%20today%20are%20trained%20on%20roughly%20the%20amount%20of%20information%20in%20the%20visual%20cortex%20of%20a%20four-year-old%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20deal%20with%20real-world%20problems%20with%20ambiguity%20and%20uncertainty%2C%20it's%20not%20just%20about%20scaling%20anymore%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20advancements%20have%20been%20slowing%20lately.%20This%20is%20due%2C%20in%20part%2C%20to%20a